  "heroImage": "/images/united-arab-emirates/the-city-lights-the-evening-dubai-wallpaper-121043ba62c0bcb098e5e3afb200b8b8.jpg",
  "headerNotes": [],
  "steps": [
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying the UAE",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/0_Normal_Summary_Graphic_1.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_desert.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/VNePq383S8THMzvK9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The UAE typically features a flat **desert landscape**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_roadlines.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/GV3fzE8unLEPjDDm6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Outer roadlines are **yellow**, middle lines either **white **or **yellow**.",
              "NOTE: Other Middle Eastern countries, like Jordan, Israel and Oman, also use these lines."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/gen3car.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/48v58xgVdQb64m2e6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "In almost all Generation 3 coverage, a **white car** with visible black roof racks was used.",
              "NOTE: The UAE is the only Middle Eastern country where a white Google car can be found."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/2022-12-14_1__281_29.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/iKpxf8krJdtA16MBA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "In Generation 4 coverage, a white **pickup truck** with a trekker camera was used for much of the coverage. In a lot of the coverage, the truck is completely [blurred out](https://maps.app.goo.gl/gz9p2N59bhqFxtvT7).",
              "NOTE: A similar truck can be found in [Qatar](https://maps.app.goo.gl/9vAjK8jA8Upvm1pq8) and [Oman](https://maps.app.goo.gl/CAfekUi6QZ6TF6bV7). In the UAE the antenna at the front of the cabin is on the middle of the car, while in Qatar it is on the left."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/UAE_Gen_4_black.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/FwkQNmdyYHL74xj8A",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "You can also find regular Generation 4 coverage taken with a **black **car. The brake light is commonly visible.",
              "NOTE: A similar Generation 4 black car can be found in [Israel](https://maps.app.goo.gl/8AR2EPX61mXVjE1M6)."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/arabic_language.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/united-arab-emirates/arabic_language.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The official language in the UAE is Arabic. Its script can be identified by its **lines and dots**.",
              "NOTE: Due to high tourism, signs in the UAE often have English writing alongside Arabic. While this is also common in Qatar and Oman, it is not common in Jordan."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/architecture.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/NvUYm7ieMn9DArty5",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Houses in residential areas are typically made of **light-coloured stone**. Reddish stones are often used for sidewalks."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_signpost.png",
              "imageLink": "https://www.google.com/maps/@25.0611912,55.707767,3a,15y,60.49h,82.37t/data=!3m6!1e1!3m4!1swL1j3pr02vFm9tlwF_OqpA!2e0!7i16384!8i8192?entry=ttu",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Many signposts in the UAE have **black-and-white stripes**.",
              "NOTE: Within the Middle East, striped signposts are also found in Oman."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_kerbs.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/xc3nWyoNAAB282bt6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Similarly, almost all curbs are **striped**. They can be either black-and-white, or black-and-yellow."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/roundabout.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/6cSPp9Gkvxqonzna8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**Divided roads** and **roundabouts** are both very commonly seen in the UAE."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_poles.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/SutBev8evrttFCzJA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Electricity poles in the UAE are mostly made of **dark brown wood**. The pole tops consist of **three insulators**, symmetrically attached to a **horizontal metal bar**.",
              "NOTE: Similar poletops can be found in Oman. Jordanian poletops may look similar, but they are usually made of grey concrete, and the insulators are more spaced out."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "pole"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_unpavedresidentialroad.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/jodYR8yVoZGDboudA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Although the UAE is a wealthy country, it is not uncommon for residential roads to be **unpaved**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/rifts.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/wdeVJfVcqZrg6iaT7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**Rifts** can occasionally be found in the UAE.",
              "NOTE: They are most commonly found in Albania, Montenegro and Senegal."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional and emirate-specific clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_coverage.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_coverage.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Coverage in the UAE is mostly limited to the **Northeastern part** of the country.",
              "NOTE: The only car coverage outside of this region exists on Sir Baniyas Island. All other remote coverage was taken by a trekker."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_dubaiskyline.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/o1QUCUumRMJSeryQ7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The skyline of Dubai is dominated by numerous **skyscrapers**, including the iconic Burj Khalifa."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_eastmountains.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/qu584qCbnNes1GQ36",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "**Mountains** are only found in the far east of the country."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/Landscape_-_Ras_al_Khaimah_Mountains.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/1B3KYMU5tXCFow9f6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "You can easily recognise the Northern part of the emirate of Ras al Khaimah thanks to the **light-coloured mountains** visible to the east."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_gulfofoman.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/V49TXbk3K4RWqp736",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "If you see **mountains to the west**, and flatness to the east, you are likely near the Gulf of Oman, in the extreme East of the country."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Spotlight",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/UAE-sir-baniyas.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/jNvE6bwu1SykMSKh9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "This rare white Google car with visible side mirrors and sparse vegetation is found on **Sir Baniyas** Island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/UAE-dubai-gen-4-trekker.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/548ZpVchkR3jcGju7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "In some parts of Dubai, including the [old town](https://goo.gl/maps/CXsP5xq4fAtX7Ds47), a Generation 4 **sidewalk trekker** was used. Sometimes, the employee\u2019s black hair is visible."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/ae_dubaisign.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/pqM2HBPmEjp7WEdp7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "These **blue** street name signs, with a narrow **metal border**, are specific to Dubai."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/UAE-al-ain-trekkers.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/xCZKgEXBKALugf2J6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The city of **Al Ain** has several trekkers, far away from the area with car coverage: two forts ([Qasr Al Muwaiji](https://goo.gl/maps/nbGPsLFqTb1terfh9) and [Al Jahili](https://goo.gl/maps/xMzzvnsvnPqw5ywR9)) and a [zoo](https://goo.gl/maps/XAVgfZVCEW1VPkUE9)."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/UAE-racetrack.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/aS9bsLjJ6cYhLGdH9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "This **racetrack** coverage is found slightly east of Abu Dhabi."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/united-arab-emirates/UAE-southern-desert-trekkers.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/mG5v9HXoYZzx9MSN8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Remote trekkers, with **sand dunes** all around, can be found in the far south of the country, between the towns of Taraq and Alyhyali."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
